This paper is about building dialog systems using neural networks, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The paper specifically focuses on improving the interpretability of the response generation process, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper proposes unsupervised learning methods using variational autoencoders (VAEs), which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions using real-world dialog datasets, which could potentially involve computer vision techniques (cs.CV) for processing visual information in the dialog. Finally, the paper's focus on improving the generation process suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE).
